WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.760
[Amit Varma]: Every year, the government presents its annual budget, and there is enormous fuss over it.

00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:14.760
[Amit Varma]: It is a media spectacle, and I wonder when some smart person in the finance ministry

00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:19.240
[Amit Varma]: will get the idea of inserting commercial breaks in between the live telecast.

00:00:19.240 --> 00:00:23.480
[Amit Varma]: I can totally imagine the finance minister saying, and now to tell you about how we will

00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:27.840
[Amit Varma]: recapitalize public sector banks, but first, a quick commercial break.

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:29.120
[Amit Varma]: This could be India's Super Bowl.

00:00:29.120 --> 00:00:34.400
[Amit Varma]: No, but seriously, it irritates me that the budget is given so much importance by people

00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:39.440
[Amit Varma]: because it reflects how much coercive power the state has over its subjects.

00:00:39.440 --> 00:00:44.000
[Amit Varma]: If the Maybap Indian state did only the things it was supposed to, and interfered nowhere

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:49.240
[Amit Varma]: else, the budget would be insignificant, provide the rule of law, and society will see to its

00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:50.520
[Amit Varma]: own prosperity.

00:00:50.520 --> 00:00:55.720
[Amit Varma]: Whatever prosperity we do achieve is usually in spite of the interfering state, rather

00:00:55.720 --> 00:00:57.880
[Amit Varma]: than helped along by the enabling state.

00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:01.920
[Amit Varma]: Anyway, that's the world we live in, and the budget does matter because the state has the

00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:05.280
[Amit Varma]: power and capacity to mess so much up.

00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:09.720
[Amit Varma]: It does also have the capacity to make things a lot better, especially when things are already

00:01:09.720 --> 00:01:14.880
[Amit Varma]: so bad because the worst things get, the greater the scope to make things better, I guess.

00:01:14.880 --> 00:01:20.240
[Amit Varma]: In such scraps of pointless hope, do people such as me find the will to go on living?

00:01:20.240 --> 00:01:22.400
[Amit Varma]: So did this budget give me any cause for hope?

00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:23.800
[Amit Varma]: No, it didn't.

00:01:23.800 --> 00:01:26.280
[Amit Varma]: But I still look at the bright side of things.

00:01:26.280 --> 00:01:32.640
[Amit Varma]: More joblessness means more people will have more time to listen to my podcast.

